This paper discusses the optimization of parameters in AlphaZero, which is a machine learning algorithm used for playing games. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also focuses on training models and evaluating their performance, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with game theory and optimization, which could be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses Othello as a game to test the algorithm, which could be considered as an application of computer vision, leading to the possibility of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a sub-category.
